The engine casing (Motorgehäuse) is in four parts: the V-shaped crankcase (Kurbelgehäuse), the lower crankcase section (Kurbelgehäuse-Unterteil) and the two cylinder heads (Zylinderköpfe). The twelve cylinders are staggered in two banks. Their numbering runs, in the direction of travel:
left bank, rear to front: cylinders 1–6;
right bank, rear to front: cylinders 7–12;
firing order (Zündfolge): 1, 12, 5, 8, 3, 10, 6, 7, 2, 11, 4, 9.
Between the casing parts, the six-throw crankshaft (Kurbelwelle) runs in seven roller bearings (Rollenlager). The connecting rods (Pleuelstangen), acting in pairs on the crankshaft, have replaceable bearing shells (Lagerschalen). The piston (Kolben) is of light alloy; the gudgeon pin (Kolbenbolzen) is fully floating.
The inclined overhead valves (schräg hängende Ventile) are worked by rocker arms (Schwinghebel), controlled by the camshafts (Nockenwellen), which are carried at seven points in the two cylinder heads.
The camshafts are driven from the crankshaft gear (Kurbelwellenrad) through an idler gear (Zwischenrad).
Built into or onto the engine are:
2 oil scavenge pumps (Ölabsaugpumpen) in the crankcase;
1 oil circulating pump (Ölumlaufpumpe);
1 oil filter (Ölfilter);
1 water pump (Wasserpumpe) and 1 dynamo (Lichtmaschine), both driven from the crankshaft by common V-belts (Keilriemen);
2 fuel pumps (Kraftstoffpumpen), driven from the crankshaft via a cam disc (Nockenscheibe);
2 Solex two-stage downdraught cross-country carburettors (Solex-Zweistufen-Fallstrom-Geländevergaser) with starting device (Anlaßvorrichtung);
1 impulse magneto (Schnappermagnetzünder);
1 electric starter (elektrischer Anlasser);
1 inertia starter (Schwungkraftanlasser).
Also provided within the engine compartment:
4 air filters (Luftfilter);
1 electric priming fuel pump (elektrische Anlaß-Kraftstoffpumpe).
